  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "It must be noted that increasing participation in the space of AI is difficult and lacks well-defined process guidance.",
    "Participatory design is challenging on its own, and the AI space adds further obstacles: Users surrender due to technical complexity, hype generates unrealistic expectations, as well as the lack of process and methods to define RAI requirements with external stakeholders.",
    "Further studies are required to make human-centred design more accessible to practitioners.",
    "Previous works have shown that several AI practitioner needs are unmet due the shortcomings of RAI guidelines (Morley et al. 2021b; Yildirim et al. 2023).",
    "By providing recommended actions and suggesting longer-term shifts in perception, we aim to mitigate these shortcomings."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Previous works have shown that several AI practitioner needs are unmet due the shortcomings of RAI guidelines (Morley et al. 2021b; Yildirim et al. 2023)."
  ]
